      "text": "NAME: OGUNKUADE JUSTINA KEHINDE COURSE: MASTER OF ARTS IN CHRISTIAN COUNSELLING TOPIC: CHRISTIAN COUNSELLING AND ETHICS NO 19 Question 2 Man is a spirit he has a soul that lives in his body. Discuss. -According to philosophical doctrine, humans are immortal spirit that temporarily inhibits physical bodies and may have influence on the physical. The Bible describes humans as consisting of a body, soul, and spirit. The Bible gives account that man Is the most accurate being. It is not based on theory but on facts. It is based on the word of the one who created man. God Himself. Genesis2:7 \u201cThen the Lord formed man of the dust from the ground, and breathed unto his nostril the breath of life\u201d. (The human spirit) and man became a soul that resides in the body. God combined the body with the spirit to create the soul. *The spirit is the breath of life that God breathed in man. And this spirit relates with God. With tis spirit man relates with the spiritual world. The spirit is the real man. Once the spirit is not there, there will be no life. There is more to the realm of the spirit than this actual life we are living in. And you cannot relate with the spirit world without having a spirit. (Humans) Soul- Our complete human soul which consists of the mind, emotion and will reside in the body. Negative thoughts reside more in the soul than positive, that is why we need to always occupy our minds with positive thoughts. The Body- Is like a container that harbor the spirit and the soul. There is a distinction between the spirit and the soul. 1 Thessalonians 5: 23 \u201cAnd the very God of peace sanctify you wholely, and I pray your whole spirit, soul and body, be preserved blameless until the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ.",
